        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When saving new table row to the database default values are filtered and not saved to the database.\nIMHO, we should not check for modified fields when inserting a new row\nReplacing two lines\n{code:title=File Zend\/Db\/Table\/Row\/Abstract.php line 400}\n$data = array_intersect_key($this->_data, $this->_modifiedFields);\n$primaryKey = $this->_getTable()->insert($data);\n{code}\nwith\n{code}\n$primaryKey = $this->_getTable()->insert($this->_data);\n{code}\nshould fix the problem"
        },
