            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25959",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragonbe",
                        "name": "dragonbe",
                        "displayName": "Michelangelo van Dam",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "fix bug for #bughuntday",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dragonbe",
                        "name": "dragonbe",
                        "displayName": "Michelangelo van Dam",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-08T06:00:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-08T06:00:48.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26894",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satanistlav",
                        "name": "satanistlav",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Anisimov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As I see the issue is not resolved yet.\nTo avoid the problem I followed this way.\nI put this lines in pre-insert logic\n\n\n{code}\nprotected function _insert()\n{\n\tforeach ($this->_table->getDefaultValues() as $k=>$v) {\n\t\t$this->_modifiedFields[$k] = true;\n\t}\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satanistlav",
                        "name": "satanistlav",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Anisimov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-02T04:49:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-02T04:49:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28843",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cortex",
                        "name": "cortex",
                        "displayName": "sebastien crocquesel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think that the issue comes when defaultSource is set to self::DEFAULT_CLASS. Then, the default value must be passed to the insert statement and thus, must be touched to become a modifiedFields.\n\nIn the Zend_Db_Table_Abstract::createRow, i would merge the $data from argument with the defaults value before the call to SetFromArray\n\nChange:\n\n} elseif ($defaultSource == self::DEFAULT_CLASS && $this->_defaultValues) {\n        \t\n            foreach ($this->_defaultValues as $defaultName => $defaultValue) {\n                if (array_key_exists($defaultName, $defaults)) {\n                    $defaults[$defaultName] = $defaultValue;\n                }\n            }\n}\n\nwith something like\n\n} elseif ($defaultSource == self::DEFAULT_CLASS && $this->_defaultValues) {\n        \t\n            foreach ($this->_defaultValues as $defaultName => $defaultValue) {\n                if (array_key_exists($defaultName, $defaults)) {\n                    $defaults[$defaultName] = $defaultValue;\n                }\n            }\n           \/\/ add the defaults value to the data, values specified in $data override defaults one \n           $data = array_merge($defaults, $data);\n        }",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cortex",
                        "name": "cortex",
                        "displayName": "sebastien crocquesel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-15T12:43:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-15T12:43:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28938",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cortex",
                        "name": "cortex",
                        "displayName": "sebastien crocquesel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Be aware that with this fix, you can no longer mix default value from the database and from the class. But I think it's not really recommended and was not the purpose of this functionnality.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cortex",
                        "name": "cortex",
                        "displayName": "sebastien crocquesel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-02-19T05:22:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-02-19T05:22:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30302",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=uniqueculture",
                        "name": "uniqueculture",
                        "displayName": "Sergei Izvorean",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem occurs due to default values aren't flagged in $_modifiedFields array. They are just assigned to $_data. Other fields that you change go through __set method and 'true' is set for each changed field in $_modifiedFields. \n\nI would create a method to set initial data:\n\nprotected function _setData(array $data) \n{\n$this->_data = $data;\n$this->_modifiedFields = array_combine(array_keys($data), array_fill(0, count($data), true));\n}\n\nthanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=uniqueculture",
                        "name": "uniqueculture",
                        "displayName": "Sergei Izvorean",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-21T12:10:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-21T12:10:53.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
